<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="prefer-vt">prefer <strong><em>vt</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /prɪ'fɜː(r)/    美 /prɪ'fɜːr/  </p>
<p>(preferred, preferred)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>更喜欢；更愿意：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Tea or coffee?
喝茶还是咖啡？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— I’d prefer tea, thanks. 
我更喜欢茶，谢谢。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She prefers her coffee black. 
她更喜欢喝清咖啡。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>prefer sb / sth to do sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I’d prefer you to start early. 
我更希望你早点出发。</p><footer>北师大⑧ – 24</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I prefer my English classes to be taught in English only. 
我希望我的英语课是全英语授课。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>prefer to do sth / doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Some people prefer to do almost everything over the Internet. 
有些人喜欢在网上做几乎一切事情。</p><footer> 2013 安徽</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I prefer shutting myself in and listening to music all day on Sunday. 
周日我喜欢一整天把自己关在屋里听音乐。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>prefer (doing) sth to (doing) sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I prefer the red dress to the green one because it fits me better. 
比起那条绿裙子，我更喜欢那条红色的，因为它更适合我。</p><footer>人教① – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I would prefer reading books to watching television.
比起看电视，我还是喜欢读书。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>prefer + that 从句：</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They preferred the money (should) be used for building schools and hospitals. 
他们更愿意拿这笔钱来建学校和医院。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I would prefer that you didn’t mention my name. 
我希望你不要提到我的名字。</p></div>

<p>注: prefer + that 从句结构中，从句中用虚拟语气。  </p>
<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>preferred  /prɪ'fəd/ adj   </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>We can eat out if you like, but I would <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (更喜欢) to stay in.  （2014 陕西）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. prefer  </p></div>